chapter.article:
1. The Parties shall gradually establish, during a transitional period ending at the latest on 1 January 2001, a free-trade area in accordance with the provisions of the present Agreement and in conformity with those of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade 1994, in particular Article XXIV of the GATT, and the Agreement Establishing the World Trade Organization. 


2. 	The objectives of the present Agreement are: 


(a) 	to promote, through the expansion of trade, the harmonious development of economic relations between the Parties and thus to foster the advance of their economic activity, the improvement of living and employment conditions, and increase of the productivity and financial stability; 


(b) 	to provide fair conditions of competition in trade between the Parties; 


(c) 	to contribute in this way, by removal of barriers to trade, to the harmonious development and expansion of the world trade.
